1. Function: addNumbers
Description: Adds two numbers and returns the result.
Example:
Named Function
```javascript
function addNumbers(a, b) {
  return a + b;
}
```
Arrow Function
```javascript
const addNumbersArrow = (a, b) => a + b;
```
2. Function: multiplyNumbers
Description: Multiplies two numbers and returns the result.
Example:
Named Function
```javascript
function multiplyNumbers(a, b) {
  return a * b;
}
```
Arrow Function
```javascript
const multiplyNumbersArrow = (a, b) => a * b;
```
3. Function: findMax
Description: Finds the maximum number from an array of numbers and returns it.
Example:
```javascript
function findMax(numbers) {
  return Math.max(...numbers);
}
```
Arrow Function
```javascript
const findMaxArrow = (numbers) => Math.max(...numbers);
```
4. Function: isPalindrome
Description: Checks if a given string is a palindrome and returns a boolean value.
Example:
```javascript
function isPalindrome(str) {
  const reversed = str.split('').reverse().join('');
  return str === reversed;
}
```
Arrow Function
```javascript
const isPalindromeArrow = (str) => {
  const reversed = str.split('').reverse().join('');
  return str === reversed;
};
```

1. Function: reverseString
Description: Reverses a given string and returns the result.
Example:
Named Function
```javascript
function reverseString(str) {
  return str.split('').reverse().join('');
}
```
Arrow Function
```javascript
const reverseStringArrow = (str) => str.split('').reverse().join('');
```
2. Function: calculateFactorial
Description: Calculates the factorial of a given number.
Example:
Named Function
```javascript
function calculateFactorial(n) {
  if (n === 0 || n === 1) {
    return 1;
  }
  return n * calculateFactorial(n - 1);
}
```
Arrow Function
```javascript
const calculateFactorialArrow = (n) => (n === 0 || n === 1) ? 1 : n * calculateFactorialArrow(n - 1);
```
